    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text>**30.3 E4 LU Decomposition**

Calculate an \\\(LU\\\) decomposition for this matrix:

\\\[{@M@}\\\]

\\\(L=\\\)[[input:S_L]] [[validation:S_L]] [[feedback:L]]

\\\(U=\\\)[[input:S_U]] [[validation:S_U]] [[feedback:U]]

Using this decomposition, solve the following system of equations \\\(Mx=r\\\). Note that you have to swap rows in \\\(r\\\) also, if you swap them in \\\(M\\\) before factorisation:

\\\({@M@}\,{@matrix([x1],[x2],[x3])@}={@rhs@}.\\\)

First, calculate the intermediate vector \\\(y\\\) with \\\(Ly=r\\\). 

\\\(y=\\\) [[input:S_y]] [[validation:S_y]] [[feedback:y]]

and then the solution \\\(x\\\) with \\\(Ux=y\\\):

\\\(x=\\\) [[input:S_x]] [[validation:S_x]] [[feedback:x]]</text>
    </questiontext>
